30P Graphite LEIP LAB EVAL-SEP17 A.I. Hawari, Y. Zhu, J.L. Wormald  32 1451     
 NDS 148, 1 (2018)    DIST-FEB18                                    32 1451     
----ENDF/B-VIII.0     MATERIAL 32                                   32 1451     
-----THERMAL NEUTRON SCATTERING DATA                                32 1451     
------ENDF-6 FORMAT                                                 32 1451     
                                                                    32 1451     
 Temperatures = 296 400 500 600 700 800 1000 1200 1600 2000 K.      32 1451     
                                                                    32 1451     
 Background                                                         32 1451     
                                                                    32 1451     
 ----------                                                         32 1451     
 This library was produced by the Low Energy Interaction Physics    32 1451     
 (LEIP) group at North Carolina State University. The thermal       32 1451     
 scattering law data for 30% porous graphite were fully developed   32 1451     
 using molecular dynamics methods [1, 2]. Vacancies were created    32 1451     
 by randomly removing atoms from the crystalline lattice. The       32 1451     
 coherent elastic cross sections were assumed to be that for a      32 1451     
 crystalline graphite structure. Ten temperatures are available in  32 1451     
 this library. The LEAPR module from NJOY code system was used to   32 1451     
 produce File 7 MT = 2, 4 data for graphite. The coherent elastic   32 1451     
 data were prepared using the cubic approximation in LEAPR/NJOY.    32 1451     
 MAT=36 and ZA=136 are used for 30% porosity reactor graphite.      32 1451     
                                                                    32 1451     
                                                                    32 1451     
